      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of 2 letters; one from Brig.
         General Rufus King to Brig. General Hector Tyndale, the other
         from Charles King to an unknown admirer of "Buffalo Bill
         Cody." In addition, there is an article from the Milwaukee 
         <title render="italic">Sentinel</title>regarding King's book 
         <title render="italic">Campaigning With Crook</title>.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <dsc type="combined">
         <head>Contents List</head>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e183">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Brig. Gen. Rufus King to Brig. Gen. Hector 
               <unitdate>1863 July 7</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>TL (transcript), 1 p.</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>Concerns surrender at Vicksburg.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e194">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Charles King to unknown admirer of "Buffalo
               Bill Cody" 
               <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>TL (transcript), 1 p.</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>Describes fight where Cheyenne Chief Hayowei was
               killed and where Cody's story of the fight differs.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
         <c01 level="item" id="d1e205">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Article from Milwaukee 
               <title render="italic">Sentinel</title>
                  <unitdate>1964 April 20</unitdate>
               </unittitle>
               <physdesc>Newsclipping</physdesc>
            </did>
            <scopecontent>
               <p>Re King's book 
               <title render="italic">Campaigning With Crook</title>.
               Reports a new edition of book has just been
               published.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c01>
      </dsc>
